[[Image:Maitreya project.jpg|frame|right|Computer-generated rendering of the proposed Maitreya Project Statue]]
The '''Maitreya Project''' is an international organisation, operating since 1990,<ref name='maitreyaproject.org/en/updates/2007-11'>{{cite news
| first=Peter
| last=Kedge
| title=Maitreya Project Update, November 2007
| date=2007-11
| publisher= Maitreya Project International I.O.M.
| url =http://www.maitreyaproject.org/en/updates/index.html
| work =Maitreya Project International website
| accessdate = 2007-11-21 }}</ref>
set up to construct a 152 metre (500&nbsp;ft) statue of the [[Maitreya]] [[Buddhahood|Buddha]], in [[Kushinagar]], [[Uttar Pradesh]], India,<ref name='taipeitimes.com/News/feat/arch/2001/07/12/93828'>{{cite news
| first=Ian
| last=Bartholomew
| title=Massive Buddha taking shape in Taiwan: The Maitreya Project aims to erect a 152 m bronze Buddha in India that it hopes will stand for 1,000 years
| date=2001-07-12
| publisher=Taipei Times
| url =http://www.taipeitimes.com/News/feat/archives/2001/07/12/93828
| work =Taipei Times
| pages =11
| accessdate = 2007-12-08 }}</ref><ref name='news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/south_asia/685179'>{{cite news
| title=Brits to build biggest Buddha
| date=2000-03-21
| publisher=British Broadcasting Corporation
| url =http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/south_asia/685179.stm
| work =BBC News: South Asia
| accessdate = 2007-12-08 }}</ref><ref name='arosltd.com/projects.php?id=24'> {{cite web
|url=http://www.arosltd.com/projects.php?id=24
|title=Regeneration: Kushingar Masterplan
|accessdate=2007-12-08
|work=Aros Architects website
|publisher=Aros Architects }}</ref> along with education and healthcare facilities for the local population. The [[design brief]] for the statue includes a [[specification]] for the statue to last for 1,000 years.<ref name='news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/south_asia/1313508'>{{cite news
| first=Priyath
| last=Liyanage
| title=India's 1,000 year Buddha underway
| date=2001-05-04
| publisher=British Broadcasting Corporation
| url =http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/south_asia/1313508.stm
| work =BBC News: South Asia
| accessdate = 2007-12-08 }}</ref>

The statue is remarkable in its size and scope; the covering over the internal steel [[truss]] structure is proposed to be of "approximately 6000 [[aluminium]]-[[bronze]] panels... cast from resin-bonded sand moulds."<ref name='arosltd.com/projects.php?id=3'> {{cite web
|url=http://www.arosltd.com/projects.php?id=3
|title=Leisure/Tourism: Maitreya Project: The Maitreya Project, India -
|accessdate=2008-03-04
|work=Aros Architects website
|publisher=Aros Architects }}</ref>

The project was initiated by the [[Foundation for the Preservation of the Mahayana Tradition]], an organisation within the [[Gelug]] school of [[Tibetan Buddhism]].

==Project partners==
The controlling corporate body is Maitreya Project International, Isle of Man.<ref name='maitreyaproject.org/en/project/structure'> {{cite web
|url=http://www.maitreyaproject.org/en/project/structure.html
|url=http://www.satyagaveshi.org/
|title=Maitreya Project Structure and Financial Summaries
|accessdate=2008-03-04
|last=Kedge
|first=Peter
|date=2008-11
|work=Maitreya Project website
|publisher=Maitreya Project International, I.O.M. }}</ref>
One of the international companies working for the Project is [[Mott macdonald|Mott MacDonald Group Limited]], providing their expertise in the tourist industry: "We have worked in all the major Indian states and have been involved in some of the most important tourism related developments in the country... we're able to deliver the complex de-signs [sic] for the Maitreya project".

==Finances==
[[File:Maitreya Project International Calif Gross Ann Rev 2001-2008.png|thumb|right|Maitreya Project International, California entity, Gross Annual Revenue 2001<U+2013>2008 in US$<ref name=CalGRA>{{Cite web
 | title = Registry Search Feature
 | work = Registry of Charitable Trusts (RCT)
 | publisher = Office of the Attorney General, State of California
 | url = http://rct.doj.ca.gov/MyLicenseVerification/Search.aspx?facility=Y
 | accessdate = 2010-06-22}}
</ref>]]
The projected budget in US dollars is: $195 million for the statue and throne building, $35 million for health and education and $20 million for development of the "750 acre" site.<ref name='http://www.maitreyaproject.org/en/project/costs'> {{cite web|url=http://www.maitreyaproject.org/en/project/costs.html |title=Project Costs |accessdate=2008-03-04 |work=Maitreya Project website |publisher=Maitreya Project International, I.O.M. }}</ref><ref name='ArosX80F_Maitreya rev'>{{cite web|url=http://www.arosltd.com/searchresults.php |title=X80F_Maitreya revised.pdf |accessdate=2008-03-04 |format=PDF |work=Aros Architects website |publisher=Aros Architects }}</ref>

==Criticism==
There has been criticism in the press about some aspects of the Project,<ref name='csmonitor.com/2007/0910/p06s02-wosc'>{{cite news | first=Daniel | last=Pepper | coauthors= | title=Indian farmers oppose giant Buddha statue | date=2007-09-10 | publisher=The First Church of Christ, Scientist | url =http://www.csmonitor.com/2007/0910/p06s02-wosc.html | work =The Christian Science Monitor | pages = | accessdate = | language = }}</ref><ref name='timesofindia.indiatimes.com/articleshow/33810155.cms'>{{cite news | first=Abdul | last=Qadir | coauthors= | title=Heavy police deployment made for Kalchakra | date=2003-01-09 | publisher=Times Internet Limited | url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/articleshow/33810155.cms | work =The Times of India | pages = | accessdate = 2008-03-04 | language = }}</ref><ref name='dharmalife.com/issue15/contemplating_navel'>{{cite news | first= | last= | coauthors= | title=Contemplating the Navel | date= | publisher=Friends of the Western Buddhist Order | url =http://www.dharmalife.com/issue15/contemplating_navel.html | work =Dharma Life, issue 15 | pages = | accessdate = 2008-03-04 | language = }}</ref><ref name='www.washingtontimes.com/article/20070920/FOREIGN/109200032/1003/foreign'>{{cite news | first= Daniel| last=Pepper |coauthors=| title=Villagers fight plan for giant Buddha | date=2007-09-20 | publisher= News World Communications, Inc.| url=http://www.washingtontimes.com/article/20070920/FOREIGN/109200032/1003/foreign |
work=The Washington Times| pages= | accessdate = 2008-04-27}}</ref><ref name='airmail_india-Questioning'>{{cite web
|url=http://www.wildriverreview.com/airmail_india-maitreya.php
|title=Bodhi Blues <U+2014> A Year in India: Questioning The Maitreya Project: What would the Buddha do?
|accessdate=2008-03-04
|last=Falcone |first=Jessica
|work=Wild River Review
|publisher=Wild River Review
| archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20080211164119/www.wildriverreview.com/airmail_india-maitreya.php
| archivedate = 2008-02-11 }}</ref><ref name='airmail_india-What would'>{{cite web
|url=http://www.wildriverreview.com/airmail_india.php
|title=Bodhi Blues <U+2014> A Year in India: What would the Buddha Do? The Debate Continues...
|accessdate=2008-03-04
|last=Falcone |first=Jessica
|work=Wild River Review
|publisher=Wild River Review
| archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20080209213314/www.wildriverreview.com/airmail_india.php
| archivedate = 2008-02 }}</ref> including the compulsory acquisition, under "India's [[Land Acquisition Act]]", by the State Government<ref name='maitreyaproject.org/en/updates/2007-11'>{{cite news | first=Peter | last=Kedge | title=Maitreya Project Update, November 2007 | date=2007-11 | publisher= Maitreya Project International I.O.M. | url =http://www.maitreyaproject.org/en/updates/index.html | work =Maitreya Project International website | accessdate = 2007-11-21 }}</ref> of {{convert|660|acre|km2}} of private land, homes and small farms; which are intended to be leased to the Project, for construction of the statue and related infrastructure, including "landscaped park housing a cathedral, monastery, convent, guesthouse, library and food halls...".<ref name="ArosX80F_Maitreya rev"/>
Peter Kedge, Director and CEO of the Maitreya Project has posted a number of replies to these criticisms.<ref name='maitreyaproject.org/en/updates/2007-11'>{{cite news | first=Peter | last=Kedge | coauthors= | title=Maitreya Project Update, November 2007 | date=2007-11 | publisher=Maitreya Project International I.O.M. | url =http://www.maitreyaproject.org/en/updates/ | work =Maitreya Project International website | pages = | accessdate = 2007-12-08 | language = }}</ref><ref name='maitreya update'>{{cite web | first=Peter | last=Kedge | url=http://www.maitreyaproject.org/en/updates/2007-09.html | title=Maitreya Project, Latest Update, September 2007 |accessdate=2007-11-10 |work=Maitreya Project International website: Maitreya Project Update |publisher=Maitreya Project International I.O.M.}}</ref><ref name='maitreyaproject.org/en/updates/2009-07.html'>{{cite news | first=Peter | last=Kedge | coauthors= | title=Maitreya Project Status & Fact Reference, September 2009 | date=2009-09 | publisher=Maitreya Project International I.O.M. | url =http://www.maitreyaproject.org/en/updates/2009-07.html | work =Maitreya Project International website | pages = | accessdate = 2009-09-26 | language = }}</ref>

